3. License Display Requirement: All products utilizing "Toro-LlaMA" or its derivative works or Toro-LlaMA Materials must visibly display the "Toro-LlaMA Community License Agreement" to ensure clear acknowledgment of the source and licensing terms.

4. Notification of Derivative Works: Any creation of derivative works or Toro-LlaMA Materials from "Toro-LlaMA" must be promptly notified to Torus Actions SAS at contact@torus-actions.fr.

5. Compliance with Laws and Regulations: All distributions of "Toro-LlaMA" or its derivative works or Toro-LlaMA Materials must comply with the applicable laws and regulations.

6. Copyright and Documentation Integrity: All distributions of "Toro-LlaMA" or its derivative works or Toro-LlaMA Materials must retain all original copyright and documentation information of both "Toro-LlaMA" and "LLAMA 2".

7. Restrictions on Competitive Usage: "Toro-LlaMA" or its derivative works or Toro-LlaMA Materials shall not be used to develop products or services that directly compete with the Torus ecosystem, unless a specific agreement is in place with Torus Actions SAS.

8. Prohibition on Improving Other Language Models: "Toro-LlaMA" or its derivative works or Toro-LlaMA Materials shall not be used to improve other language models, except for "Toro-LlaMA" and its derivative works or Toro-LlaMA Materials.

9. Additional Commercial Terms: If the number of active users per month of the products or services utilizing "Toro-LlaMA" or its derivative works or Toro-LlaMA Materials exceeds 1 million, an additional license must be requested from Torus Actions SAS. For over 700 million active users, an additional license from Meta is required.

10. Termination Clause: This Agreement may be terminated by Torus Actions SAS upon any breach of these terms and conditions or the core terms of the "LLAMA 2 Community License Agreement".

By agreeing to this License, you acknowledge and agree to adhere to both the core principles of the "LLAMA 2 Community License Agreement" and the supplementary terms and conditions specified herein for the use of "Toro-LlaMA".
